  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\nI find the contents of the existing [how-to](https://github.com/quarkusio/quarkus/blob/main/docs/src/main/asciidoc/_templates/template-howto.adoc) and [tutorial](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/quarkusio/quarkus/main/docs/src/main/asciidoc/_templates/template-tutorial.adoc) doc templates confusing. \r\n\r\nThey contain both _template_ and _instructional_ text, without a clear distinction between the two. Some useful template elements seem to be missing, such as prerequisites and procedure sections. I'd like to separate the instructional text from the template text by moving the instructional to a separate document. \r\n\r\n### Implementation ideas\r\n\r\n_No response_",
